Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{300%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm fries (peeling optional).

Pop them onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Zest the @lemon{1}(zested). Cut half into thick wedges and juice the rest.

Cut the @broccoli{1}(cut into florets) into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.

Pat the @hake{250%g} dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Lay the hake onto a lined baking tray. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling
raw fish. Drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper.

Pop onto the top shelf and bake until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The fish is
cooked when opaque in the middle.

== Lemon Mustard Sauce ==

Place a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat with @butter{1%tbsp} (double for 4p).

When hot, add @flour{1%tbsp} (double for 4p) and stir to mix thoroughly.

Add the @mustard{1%sachet}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and @water{100%ml} (double for 4p) and bring
to a boil.

Allow to reduce for ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat and mix in the @honey{1%sachet} and
lemon zest.

Add lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste. Set aside and cover to keep warm.

== Pan-fried Broccoli ==

Place a #medium pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the broccoli and fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of water and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Allow to cook until the broccoli is tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Plate up the hake with broccoli and sweet potato fries alongside.

Drizzle over the lemon mustard sauce.

Serve with remaining lemon wedges.